From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000002 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Emil Renner Berthing <emil.renner.berthing@canonical.com>
Date: Wed, 6 Aug 2025 14:40:38 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 02/11] dt-bindings: riscv: add VLSI VSRVES01 board compatibles

Add a board-level binding for the VLSI VSRVES01 SoC family.  The first
board supported is the CAT Board reference design (vlsi,vsrves01-catboard)
which uses the vlsi,vsrves01 SoC as the compatible-string fallback.

This is a stub binding that only asserts the root compatible string;
detailed SoC and peripheral bindings live in their own files.

Depends on: dt-bindings vendor-prefix "vlsi,"

Origin: esmil/linux vsrv branch ee42a760960a

Signed-off-by: Emil Renner Berthing <emil.renner.berthing@canonical.com>
Signed-off-by: Sungjoon Moon <sumoon@seoulsaram.org>
---
 .../devicetree/bindings/riscv/vlsi.yaml       | 27 +++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 27 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 Documentation/devicetree/bindings/riscv/vlsi.yaml

diff --git a/Documentation/devicetree/bindings/riscv/vlsi.yaml b/Documentation/devicetree/bindings/riscv/vlsi.yaml
new file mode 100644
index 00000000000000..25b13c8e3308ac
--- /dev/null
+++ b/Documentation/devicetree/bindings/riscv/vlsi.yaml
@@ -0,0 +1,27 @@
+# SPDX-License-Identifier: (GPL-2.0-only OR MIT)
+%YAML 1.2
+---
+$id: http://devicetree.org/schemas/riscv/vlsi.yaml#
+$schema: http://devicetree.org/meta-schemas/core.yaml#
+
+title: VLSI SoC-based boards
+
+maintainers:
+  - Emil Renner Berthing <emil.renner.berthing@canonical.com>
+
+description:
+  VLSI SoC-based boards
+
+properties:
+  $nodename:
+    const: '/'
+  compatible:
+    oneOf:
+      - items:
+          - enum:
+              - vlsi,vsrves01-catboard
+          - const: vlsi,vsrves01
+
+additionalProperties: true
+
+...
-- 
